Package io.prometheus.client.metrics

Interface Summary
Metric.Builder<B,M> A Metric.Builder is used to create a Metric's descriptor, which describes everything about the metric: name, required label dimensions (i.e., metric cardinality), docstring, etc.
Metric.Child Metric.Child is a concrete metric, the thing you mutate.
 

Class Summary
Counter Counter is a Metric that tracks the addition or subtraction of a value from itself.
Counter.Builder Define the characteristics for this Counter.
Counter.Serializer Deprecated.
Gauge Gauge is a Metric that reports instantaneous values based on external state.
Gauge.Builder Define the characteristics for this Gauge.
Gauge.Serializer Deprecated.
Metric<M extends Metric,C extends Metric.Child,P extends Metric.Partial> A Metric is the base type of all Prometheus metrics.
Summary Summary is a Metric that samples events over sliding windows of time.
Summary.Builder  
Summary.Serializer Deprecated.
 

Exception Summary
Metric.IllegalLabelDeclarationException Metric.IllegalLabelDeclarationException is used in cases whereby the author of a metric declares an illegal label name.
